     <p class="headline">Study in the U.S.</p>
     <p> The DMD Private High School Program offers students, age 13-19 years old, the opportunity to study and live in the United States.</p>

 <p> The DMD/PHP Academic Year Program (AYP 10) and the Semester Program (AYP 5) are designed to provide foreign students with an intensive cultural and academic experience in an American family or boarding environment.</p>

  <p>DMD/PHP places students in all areas of the United States and has qualified Local Contacts throughout the country to work closely with the exchange students, host families and private schools.</p>

  <p>DMD/PHP also works with a network of independent international educational partners who provide information, screening and orientations for prospective applicants.</p>

  <p>If you are interested in experiencing American life by participating in a DMD/PHP Program, go to the <a href="contactUs.cfm" class="menu2">"contact us"</a> page to fill out your information and a representative from your home country will contact you.</p><br />
